5:

shopping district as a whole isn't

The purpose of White Fest is to show
appreciation for those you care for,
correct?
21:
Y-yeah, that's the idea. Mostly you
give sweets as a present to the

24:
In that case, appealing to emotion

30:
Welcome home, Dad! I behaved all
day, just like you told me to!
34:
Yeah, everything's fine. See? I can

Anyone else feel like hurling, or just

Chairman, you... you shouldn't... But...
Aaahhh...
54:
Heh. Was my acting not a thing of
beauty?
59:
Suizen! If you're here... does that
mean that's a shikigami over on
stage?
63:
No, this one here is the shikigami.
Acting like that requires more
finesse than my shikigami is
currently capable of.
67:
I-I guess that makes sense... You're
really drawing the crowd in with
your skills.
72: Is there something you'd like to say?
77:
Nah, not really. Not like you'd listen

81:
Do you think it pathetic that I,
someone without parents, am
acting like I know what familial love

85:
Now you're just putting words in my
mouth. If that's what you think I'm
thinking, then you're off the mark.
88:
...Not gonna lie though. This whole

96:
It appears that the town is
populated by quite a number of
orphans. I've realized my current
strategy is in poor taste and have
decided to look for other options.
99:
You know, Nimbus was only worried

loud.
104:
Mhmm. He wasn't the only one.
Mizuchi also voiced a few concerns.
106:
Do I truly appear to be taking on
more than I can handle?
110: Well, it wouldn't be the first time...
115:
I see. This was all meant to be a way
for me to relax, if you'll believe it.
125:
I'm not. Consider that, as chairman
of the Diviners' Commission, I am
normally beholden to the opinions
of my superiors and subordinates.
127:
It's honestly refreshing to be able to
direct matters however I please.
132:
In other words, all this work is
actually... fun?
137:
I suppose. It reminds me a lot of
moving pieces around a shogi
board, so yes... I would say I'm
enjoying myself.
150:
Well, don't let me get in the way of
your fun.
152: Actually... Won't you let me join in?
156:
Everything's better with friends,
right? Not gonna lie, I felt a little left
out when I was racking my brains
for an idea, and you came up

161:
In that case, why don't we come up
with another sweet as our next
strategy?
171:
Er, do you really have to be so
precise with your measurements?
Pretty sure the recipe just says 
"a heaping spoonful."
174:
Of course. It's the fault of the recipe
maker for being so careless with
vague instructions.
176:
Not all of us are skilled enough to
get by on instinct like you, Alk.
181:
This is turning out to be tougher
than I expected it to be...
184:
Heheh. I won't hear any complaints
now.
188: What the hell're those two up to?
197:
Indeed. It seems we needn't have
worried.
211:
Whoa! That was awesome! You're so
good at this, Suizen!
215:
You don't need to compliment me
every time I flip the skillet.
